A 24-year-old suspect is expected to appear in the Mamelodi Magistrate’s Court on Monday in connection with the alleged brutal murder of his father. It is reported that the suspect was arrested at his home on Sunday. Mamelodi East police spokesperson Captain Michael Mbewe said: “It is alleged the deceased overheard the suspect and his mother arguing inside the house when he attempted to intervene to calm the situation.” “The suspect allegedly became more angered and grabbed a spade and hacked his father to death.” The deceased was rushed to a local hospital and allegedly died on arrival. -TNA Reporter